PRESS RELEASE

FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE

SkillsUSA Officers for the 2020-20201 School Year

Woodland, Calif., May 28, 2020 ‚Äì The Pioneer High School SkillsUSA Chapter is proud to announce the election of its officer team for the 2020-2021 school year.

Our new officers are:

President: Manuel Maravilla

Vice President: Edward Sokolow Ochoa

Treasurer: Eric Neilson

Secretary: India Fischer

Reporter: Yasivi Gutierrez

Parliamentarian: Stephanie Maravilla

Please join us in congratulating the new officers on their election. They are excited to lead the award-winning chapter into the new school year, and are ready to face the new challenges posed by the unknowns of COVID-19.

SkillsUSA is a student leadership and skills organization. Founded in 1965 as VICA, the Pioneer High School chapter was founded in 2006, and features competitions in subjects such as computer networking, computer repair, computer programming, culinary arts, commercial baking, extemporaneous speaking, prepared speech, job interview, and other contests.

###

post_text:
Trustees Considering Cancelling Non-essential Activities

The Board of Trustees met this morning to discuss and consider the recommendations from the Yolo County Health Department to organizations on preventative measures to address the spread of the coronavirus. This discussion included the question as to whether or not WJUSD should cancel non-essential activities.

I want to be clear that, as of this morning, the Board of Trustees has NOT yet made a decision to cancel non-essential activities. Non-essential activities are to continue as planned until further notice.

There is a special board meeting scheduled tomorrow evening at 6:00 PM in the board room and the Board has directed me to present a resolution for their consideration that reflects their concerns around the impacts of this decision for our students, staff, and community.

Thanks,
Tom Pritchard
Superintendent
Woodland Joint Unified School District

Woodland Joint USD will be participating in the Yolo County Office of Education's annual Employee Recognition Programs. The purpose of the program is to pay tribute to the tireless efforts of school district employees. Nominations are now being accepted for the following categories:

Individual Excellence Award
Program Excellence Award
Salute to Educator Award

Nominations are due to the Human Resources Department by 5:00 p.m. on February 21, 2020. They are accepted by any district employee, parent, or district volunteer. Nomination forms are available on the WJUSD website under Human Resources Department (link: https://www.wjusd.org/Departments/Human-Resources/Excellence-in-Educations-Form/index.html)

Winners will be recognized at the Annual Yolo County School Boards Association (YCSBA) sponsored Excellence in Education (EIE) Awards event being held on Monday, April 27, 2020 at the YCOE Conference Center.

PRESS RELEASE

Woodland Joint Unified School District Community Town Hall Meetings

Woodland, Calif., October 14, 2019 ‚Äì The Woodland Joint Unified School District seeks community input in the development of the new three-year Local Control Accountability Plan (LCAP). The LCAP is a continuous improvement plan that outlines how the district will meet student and community needs. The District requests community presence at two upcoming Town Hall meetings. Please attend one of the following:

Date: October 15, 2019
Time: 6 ‚Äì 7:30 pm
Location: Pioneer High School Cafeteria

Date: October 22, 2019
Time: 6 ‚Äì 7:30 pm
Location: Woodland High School Commons

Spanish translation and childcare will be available. Please contact the Educational Services Department at 530-406-3253 for more information. Christina Lambie, Executive Director of Teaching and Learning stated, "Community voice is essential to our Local Control Accountability Plan development and we look forward to hearing from a diverse group of stakeholders."

This is the fifth school that has partnered with the Kiwanis Club as we work together to instill the love of reading in young children!
